qas.question: What make and model aircraft was Air Force Flight 8610?
What aircraft had an incident with Air Force Flight 8610?
What call sign does an Air Force aircraft have when a president is traveling on it?
What was the name of the Lockheed C-121 Constellation that carried Eisenhower?
In what year was Eisenhower involved in an incident while flying?

context: Over New York City in <a4_0>1953<a4_0/>, <a1_0>Eastern Airlines Flight 8610<a1_0/>, a commercial flight, had a near miss with Air Force Flight 8610, a <a0_0>Lockheed C-121 Constellation<a0_0/> known as <a3_0>Columbine II<a3_0/>, while the latter was carrying President Eisenhower. This prompted the adoption of the unique call sign <a2_0>Air Force One<a2_0/>, to be used whenever the president is on board any US Air Force aircraft. Columbine II is the only presidential aircraft to have ever been sold to the public and is the only remaining presidential aircraft left unrestored and not on public display.
